Usage: checkFiller [-help] [-area <box>] [-file <fileName>]
                   [-horizontal_max_length] [-powerDomain <name>]
                   [-vertical_stack_max_length]
                   [-reportGap <value> | -adjacentFiller1]

-help                          # Prints out the command usage
-adjacentFiller1               # Check if two or more single site width fillers
                               # are plac adjacent to each other (bool, optional)
-area <box>                    # area in which the command needs to be run
                               # (box, optional)
-file <fileName>               # Write checkFiller output to file
                               # (string, optional)
-horizontal_max_length         # check if horizontal stack length violates max
                               # limit (bool, optional)
-powerDomain <name>            # Power domain name (string, optional)
-reportGap <value>             # Generate checkFiller output only for the
                               # specified microns (float, optional)
-vertical_stack_max_length     # check if vertical stack length violates max
                               # limit (bool, optional)